{"key":"processedPost-12432933","value":{"id":12432933,"first":12379669,"last":12578952,"when":1271887206,"utime":"04/22/10 01:00 AM","content":"Yes, it's grounding the chassis of the motor/blower and that's what you want.&nbsp; The idea is if the motor shorts out or a wire comes loose and touches the metal, it will trip the breaker.&nbsp; If the metal wasn't grounded, the breaker wouldn't trip and you could get electrocuted from touching it.&nbsp; It looks ready to plug in.&nbsp; Once you see that it runs, route your cord through the knockout into that junction box, and then put the cover on.&nbsp; Get a romex connector to act as a strain relief and to protect the cord.<br /><br />The foam is to help seal around the seat.&nbsp; Your box is going to need a lip at the exit end of the filter to get a good seal.&nbsp; You don't want air bypassing the filter and coming out around the edges.<br />RR","title":"Re: Need help building a flowhood.","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}